      "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index Comparison Against Experimental Benchmark",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values were compared against in-vitro experimental measurements for the FDA generic centrifugal pump across 5 flow-speed operating points. RH values ranged from 0.71 to 0.94, all satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Experimental data were obtained from published FDA benchmark studies. The comparison showed good agreement within measurement uncertainty bounds.",
